@node "Introduction" "Introduction to Index View"

  @{b}@{u}Introduction@{ub}@{uu}

  Mlocator is a small utility, which allows to compute distance and
direction (azimuth) between two radio stations. 

  Main features of MLocator:
    - Can compute grid LOC to Longtitude/Latitude and vice versa.
    - Magic User Interface.
    - Tooltypes support.
    - Now generate T:Direction file which contains azimuth for
      antennas.
      If you know ARexx then it will be very easy for you to write some
      script for your rotator interface.
    - Can work from CLI.
    - It's freeware.

  Someone asked me why I wrote MLocator. It's true that on Aminet is
Cibils but there was a few reasons:
    - I'm a really HAM radio operator, not a CB fan (so I don't need to
      convert channel of my RIG to frequency)
    - I found some difference between quantity of distance of MLocator
      and other programs. In my procedure which compute distance I based
      on a very popular book in Poland "Poradnik ultrakrotkofalowca"
      by Zdzislaw Bienkowski SP6LB. I belive in this book and
      mathematical formulas in it.
@endnode

