@node "Usage" "How to use Index View"

  @{b}@{u}Usage@{ub}@{uu}

  from CLI:

  Locator LOC/K LOC1/K LOC2/K LATI/K LONG/K

  e.g.:

  Locator LOC KO00AC

      - will compute Latitude/Longtitude for KO00AC

  Locator LATI 50.0600N LONG 20.0224E

      - will compute grid LOC for given coordinates (in DD.MMSS format)

  Locator LOC1 KO00AB LOC2 KO00AC

      - will compute distance and direction between two locators

  from Workbench:

      You can select string field by click mouse button and type on
  keyboard your locator. Also you can enter latitude/longtitude. If you
  wrote something in string field you have to press "ENTER" key. You can
  change field with "TAB" key.

  Tooltypes:

  LOC1 - Locator of 1st station.

  LOC2 - Locator of 2nd station.

  e.g.:

  LOC1=KO00AC
  LOC2=KO90XC

  After start MLocator will set this locators as default.
@endnode

